# Trivy ignore list — base-OS CVEs in the node:22-slim (Debian bookworm) base image
# that have NO fix available AND no runtime path in our Node-only proto server
# (the container runs `node prototype/netserver.mjs` — no perl, no terminal UI, etc.).
# Each is an accepted, documented risk; re-review whenever the base image is bumped.
# Ties to audit SD-5.1 (minimal image) / F-15 (base-image hygiene). The fixable image
# CVEs (corepack/pnpm cache, global npm) are removed in the Dockerfile, not ignored.

# zlib1g: the vulnerable minizip code is NOT built by Debian → not applicable.
CVE-2023-45853

# ncurses / libtinfo6: no fixed version; terminal library is unused by the server.
CVE-2025-69720

# perl-base: perl is never invoked at runtime; no fixed version published.
CVE-2026-42496
CVE-2026-8376
CVE-2026-42497
CVE-2026-48962
CVE-2026-9538
